g.text: A web crawler is a program that automatically traverses the web by downloading web pages and following links from one
page to another. It is used to index the web for search engines, collect data for research, or monitor websites
1. Crawl the web starting from a given set of seed URLs.
2. Extract text data from each web page and store the text for later processing.
2. scalable - should be able to handle the 10B pages in a day
3. fault tolerant - Be able to handle large number of failures when fetching pages, be able to resume if needed
Input: the input to your system
Output: the output of your system
- output: store parsed text content from webpages for later processing
1. Data enters the system by X
N. Data is stored in W
1. list of URLs are fed into the URL frontier
2. Resolve DNS for the given url to scrape
3. Webpage is fetched for a given url.
4. Text is extracted from the webpage
5. Webpage content is stored in a DB.
6. Additional URL links are extracted from the webpage and added back to the URL frontiner.
